    "rationale": "Despite six credibility factors remaining at achieved level 1 (not assessed) and the highest-priority factor (Relevance of QOI) showing a gap from achieved level 3 to required level 5, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ demonstrates a 13% margin to the clinical NIH threshold and three ValidationResults provide full provenance to experimental evidence. The orphan Claim (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-acceptable) is considered adequately supported by the ValidationResult provenance chains, though no direct prov:wasDerivedFrom link from the Claim to Evidence was established.",
